article.description: Marcel Pettway made 9 of 10 shots and finished with 26 points and 11 rebounds to help Bryant beat Fairleigh Dickinson 85-80 on Monday night.
article.headline: Pettway scores 26, Bryant beats Fairleigh Dickinson 85-80
article.linkText: Pettway scores 26, Bryant beats Fairleigh Dickinson 85-80
article.story: TEANECK, N.J. -- Marcel Pettway made 9 of 10 shots and finished with 26 points and 11 rebounds to help Bryant beat Fairleigh Dickinson 85-80 on Monday night. Pettway hit all seven of his field-goal attempts in the first half and had 18 points. Hunter Ware added 17 points by the break as Bryant held a 45-30 lead after shooting 60 percent from the field. Curtis Oakley gave Bryant a 76-59 lead with 5:10 remaining but the Bulldogs went without a field goal the rest of the way. Bryant hit 9 of 16 from the line down the stretch. Ware finished with 19 points and seven rebounds for Bryant (5-10, 2-0 Northeast), which only played seven players. Nisre Zouzoua and Shane McLaughlin scored 13 and 10, respectively, off the bench. Darian Anderson led Fairleigh Dickinson (5-8, 1-1) with 23 points. Earl Potts Jr. added 18 points and Stephan Jiggetts had 17.
